    "# 03 - First derivative (catch the take-off)\n",
    "\n",
    "**The idea:** the daily signal is bumpy. We smooth it, then take the\n",
    "**first derivative** = how much it changed since yesterday (think 'speed').\n",
    "When that speed jumps well above normal, attention is accelerating - that is\n",
    "the inflection / take-off point. We mark those days in red.\n",
    "\n",
    "You can run this on EITHER signal from notebook 02 by setting `VALUE_COLUMN`:\n",
    "`mention_count` (raw) or `weighted_count` (upvote-weighted).\n",
    "\n",
    "Reads `data/processed/daily_ticker_counts.parquet` (made by notebook 02)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "cell-1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
